The pilot reported that during the landing roll, the airplane veered right and the pilot 
attempted to correct back to the centerline using the flight controls. The airplane exited the 
right side of the runway, ground looped and sustained substantial damage to the left wing and 
left aileron.
The pilot reported no preimpact mechanical failures or malfunctions with the airframe or 
engine that would have precluded normal operation.
The pilot's loss of directional control during the landing roll, which resulted in a runway 
excursion, and a ground loop.
